1
Intellectual Property Management


Patent Strategy & Portfolio Management: Work closely with Product and Engineering teams to identify, capture, and strategize patentable innovations. Conduct brainstorming sessions to identify IP arising from product roadmaps and new features.
Patent Prosecution: Serve as the primary liaison between external patent counsel and internal technical experts. Draft, review, and coordinate patent applications and claims with the United States Patent and Trademark Office (prior USPTO experience required). Maintain invention disclosure policies and procedures.
Patent Review Board: Act as a key member of Freshworks' Patent Review Committee, evaluating invention disclosures and making strategic decisions on patent filings.
Trademark Management: Prepare, file, and manage trademark applications globally. Conduct trademark clearance searches, monitor registrations, and manage enforcement actions including cease-and-desist letters, takedown notices, and cybersquatting matters. Must have experience with United States trademark process and Madrid protocol for international trademark registration.
Brand Counsel: Advise Marketing and Product teams on branding strategies, trademark implications of new product names, and brand protection initiatives.
IP Litigation Support: Assist internal and external counsel with patent and trademark litigation, claims review, oppositions, and dispute resolution matters.
Open Source & Software Compliance


Open Source Compliance: Advise Engineering teams on open-source software (OSS) license compliance, including GPL, MIT, Apache, and other licenses. Support operationalization of OSS compliance processes and tooling.
Copyright & DMCA: Handle inbound DMCA notices, copyright infringement claims, and takedown processes.
Product Counselling & Commercialization


Product Development Advice: Provide legal guidance throughout the product lifecycle from ideation to launch on IP ownership, licensing, regulatory compliance, and risk mitigation.
Product Launch Support: Partner with the Senior Product Counsel in conducting legal due diligence for new product launches and features. Develop and maintain product release checklists, playbooks, and scalable legal processes.
Commercial Agreements: Support the commercial legal team in drafting and updating IP related provisions in contract templates, customer agreements, and playbooks (e.g., licensing terms, IP ownership, indemnities, warranties).
Third-Party Integrations & Partnerships: Support the commercial legal team in drafting, reviewing, and negotiating agreements related to product development, integrations, developer tools, APIs, third-party software, and technology.
Privacy, Data Security & Regulatory Compliance


Privacy & Data Protection: Advise on privacy and data security matters, including compliance with GDPR, CCPA, DORA and other global data protection regulations. Collaborate with Privacy and Security teams on product features involving data collection, processing, and storage.
Legal Updates on IP & AI: Monitor legal and regulatory developments affecting IP, product development, open source, SaaS, AI and technology sectors. Provide timely updates and actionable guidance to stakeholders. Provide guidance on responsible AI development and deployment.
Regulatory Review: Review marketing materials, web properties, product communications, and documentation for IP, regulatory, and compliance considerations.
Cross-Functional Collaboration 


Trusted Business Partner: Build strong, trusted relationships with Product, Engineering, Marketing, Sales, and other business stakeholders. Serve as a strategic advisor to the teams you support.
Process Improvement: Drive continuous improvement of legal processes, templates, and playbooks to enable scalability and operational efficiency.
Training & Education: Educate internal teams on IP best practices, compliance requirements, and risk management strategies.
