5
1. Legal Documentation & Coordination
Prepare LOIs (Letters of Intent) and assist in drafting, reviewing, and finalizing lease agreements.
Coordinate with the Legal team for agreement closures, clarifications, and compliance-related documentation.
Communicate and follow up with store landlords for agreement execution and other required documents.
2. Statutory Registrations & Licenses
Obtain and renew Shops & Establishment Certificates for all existing and new stores.
Manage APOB (Additional Place of Business) registrations under GST for store openings.
Apply for and renew Trade Licenses from local municipal authorities.
Handle Fire NOC applications, renewals, and inspections.
Process approvals and documentation for Signage Licenses for store branding and hoardings.
3. Labor & Tax Compliance
Ensure compliance with all labour laws, including maintaining statutory registers and submitting required filings.
Manage Professional Tax (PT) registrations, monthly/annual payments, and return filing.
Coordinate with internal HR and Finance teams to ensure timely completion of all labour-related compliances.
4. Compliance Monitoring & Record Management
Maintain accurate and updated records of all store-related statutory documents, licenses, and approvals.
Track due dates for renewals and ensure timely submissions to avoid penalties.
Support internal and external audits by providing necessary compliance documentation.
